cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in medical image analysis, specifically in contour detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design principles and motivations of CNNs, which suggests a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and limitations of current methods, which could fit under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the segmentation of objects from radiology and pathology images, which could fit under cs.MM (Multimedia).
